Quote: The shearer who takes the last sheep (called the 'cobbler') calls out 'Sheep-O!'
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1949
Source: High Country Days
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 193
Edition:
Quote: Cobbler: the last sheep in a shearer's pen is called the cobbler. It is usually a tough one - hard shearing - and consequently any very hard shearing sheep are called cobblers.
